{{Infobox journal | title = The Chinese Journal of International Politics | cover = | discipline = [[International relations]] | abbreviation = Chin. J. Int. Polit. | editor = [[Yan Xuetong]] | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2006â€“present | impact = 1.312 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://cjip.oxfordjournals.org/ | link1 = http://cjip.oxfordjournals.org/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://cjip.oxfordjournals.org/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1750-8916 | eISSN = 1750-8924 | OCLC = 76903874 | LCCN = 2007202849 }} '''''The Chinese Journal of International Politics''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published quarterly by [[Oxford University Press]] for the study of international relations based on modern methodology, historical studies and policy-oriented research. Most of its articles are either related to China or have implications for Chinese foreign policy.<ref>{{cite web | title = The Chinese Journal of International Politics: Home page | url = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayJournal?jid=INT | website = cjip.oxfordjournals.org | publisher = [[Oxford University Press|Oxford Journals]] | access-date = 29 January 2016 }}</ref> It was established in 2006 and the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Yan Xuetong]] ([[Tsinghua University]]).<ref>{{cite web | title = The Chinese Journal of International Politics: Editorial board | url = http://www.oxfordjournals.org/our_journals/cjip/editorial_board.html | website = cjip.oxfordjournals.org | publisher = [[Oxford University Press|Oxford Journals]] | access-date = 29 January 2016 }}</ref>
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in: * [[EBSCOhost]] * [[Social Sciences Citation Index]] * [[SCOPUS]] * The Standard Periodical Directory
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2014 [[impact factor]] of 1.312, ranking it 21st out of 85 journals in the category "Political Science".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Political Science |title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
